<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Chicken Note</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="edn170">  170  The woman describes in detail, as women will, Ann's fussy preparations to go out on the town. &lsquo;First she let her hair fal and down it flussed to her feet its teviots winding coils&rsquo; and so on. The description probably owes something to the <i>Iliad</i>, XIV: </p><p class="set"> <i>Juno prepared to beguile Zeus. With ambrosia did she cleanse every stain from her winsome body; and anoint herself with olive oil and with her hands plaited her shining tresses and she girdled it with a girdle arrayed in a hundred tassels; and she set earrings in her pierced ears and with a veil over all the peerless goddess veiled herself.</i>  </div>
